WEBVTT

00:00.322 --> 00:01.280
Morgan? I'm sorry I didn't
do what I said I would

00:01.410 --> 00:02.281
with the Tower.

00:02.411 --> 00:03.282
You got everybody

00:03.412 --> 00:04.196
onto the rafts.

00:04.326 --> 00:05.240
That's all that matters.

00:05.371 --> 00:06.459
I've been hearing some chatter

00:06.589 --> 00:07.634
-[Crying]
-on the radio and...

00:07.764 --> 00:09.418
I think it might be PADRE.

00:09.549 --> 00:11.594
I think PADRE is real
and I think

00:11.725 --> 00:14.119
we might actually have
someplace to go to.

00:14.249 --> 00:15.033
Alicia!

00:15.163 --> 00:16.425
Get on the raft!
-No!

00:16.556 --> 00:17.948
I don't know
how fast I'll turn.

00:18.079 --> 00:20.299
I don't know how much
longer I have left.

00:20.429 --> 00:22.040
It's up to you
[Voice breaking] to make sure

00:22.170 --> 00:23.693
everything
we've been through

00:23.824 --> 00:24.955
means something.

00:25.086 --> 00:28.655
♪

00:30.700 --> 00:34.356
[Heavy breathing, wheezing]

00:35.749 --> 00:38.665
[Coughing]

00:47.630 --> 00:49.589
Voice [over intercom]:
You made it.

00:49.589 --> 00:52.635
You don't sound
like you're doing so hot.

00:52.635 --> 00:55.421
We can help with that.

00:55.421 --> 00:59.773
But first, you have to decide
if you want to be part of this.

00:59.773 --> 01:02.080
And if so, whether
you're willing to do

01:02.080 --> 01:04.995
what needs to be done.

01:04.995 --> 01:07.041
To get the thing
we know you want.

01:07.041 --> 01:09.348
[Electricity buzzing]

01:09.348 --> 01:19.314
♪

01:19.314 --> 01:22.012
[Birds calling in distance]

01:22.012 --> 01:24.754
[Walker growling in distance]

01:42.076 --> 01:44.600
[Growling continues]

01:44.948 --> 01:46.820
[Walkie-talkie beeps]

01:46.820 --> 01:49.127
Can anybody hear me?

01:49.127 --> 01:51.433
[Static]

01:53.392 --> 01:55.263
Is anybody out there?

01:58.136 --> 01:59.789
Anybody?

01:59.789 --> 02:02.488
[Baby crying]

02:06.448 --> 02:07.884
Okay.

02:07.884 --> 02:09.756
I got you.

02:09.756 --> 02:11.236
I know.

02:11.236 --> 02:12.933
You're hungry, right?

02:16.241 --> 02:17.894
We're gonna go shopping.

02:17.894 --> 02:19.374
Hey, look.

02:19.374 --> 02:21.420
Should we take Mama with us?

02:21.420 --> 02:23.944
Huh?

02:23.944 --> 02:26.381
Grace:
♪ Sittin' in the mornin' sun♪

02:26.381 --> 02:28.905
Look what we got.

02:28.905 --> 02:33.388
♪ I'll be sittin' when
the evening comes♪Got it?

02:33.388 --> 02:37.349
♪ Watchin' the ships roll in♪[Walker growling]

02:37.349 --> 02:41.048
♪ Then I watch 'em
roll away again♪

02:41.048 --> 02:42.702
♪ Yeah♪

02:42.702 --> 02:46.140
♪ I'm sittin' on the dock
of the bay♪

02:46.140 --> 02:50.536
♪ Watchin' the tide roll away♪[Growling]

02:50.536 --> 02:55.280
♪ Ooh, I'm just sittin'
on the dock of the bay♪

02:55.280 --> 02:59.327
♪ Wastin' time♪

02:59.327 --> 03:01.068
♪

03:01.068 --> 03:05.638
♪ I left my home in Georgia♪

03:05.638 --> 03:10.425
♪ Headed for the Frisco Bay♪

03:10.425 --> 03:14.560
♪ 'Cause I've had nothin'
to live for♪

03:14.560 --> 03:18.477
♪ It look like nothin's
gonna come my way♪

03:18.477 --> 03:20.130
♪ Mm♪

03:20.130 --> 03:23.482
♪ Sittin' on the dock
of the bay♪

03:23.482 --> 03:27.660
♪ Watchin' the tide roll away♪

03:27.660 --> 03:29.270
♪ Ooh♪

03:29.270 --> 03:32.795
♪ I'm sittin' on the dock
of the bay♪

03:32.795 --> 03:36.973
♪ Wastin' time♪

03:36.973 --> 03:39.280
[Gate creaks]

03:39.280 --> 03:46.853
♪

03:46.853 --> 03:49.072
[Door creaks]

03:52.728 --> 03:54.861
[Door closes]

04:10.224 --> 04:12.966
[Baby fussing]

04:17.100 --> 04:18.319
It's okay.

04:18.319 --> 04:21.279
Woman: [Muffled]
I'm here. Where are you?

04:28.895 --> 04:30.940
Jim, where are you?

04:30.940 --> 04:32.812
What are you doing here?

04:32.812 --> 04:39.297
♪

04:39.297 --> 04:41.603
I'm just looking
for food.

04:41.603 --> 04:43.649
[Baby fussing]Well, I don't have any.

04:43.649 --> 04:49.742
♪

04:49.742 --> 04:51.004
Okay.

04:51.004 --> 04:52.919
[Weapon clinks]

04:52.919 --> 04:55.138
♪

04:55.138 --> 04:57.837
How far along are you?

04:57.837 --> 04:59.621
Oh, my name is Morgan.

04:59.621 --> 05:01.928
This is my daughter, Mo.

05:01.928 --> 05:05.323
♪

05:05.323 --> 05:06.585
Ava.

05:06.585 --> 05:07.847
Okay.

05:07.847 --> 05:09.631
Ava, I think
we can help each other.

05:09.631 --> 05:12.634
You want my help?Yeah.

05:12.634 --> 05:14.897
Take that little girl
and get as far away
from here as you can.

05:14.897 --> 05:16.638
Oh, I can't do that.

05:16.638 --> 05:20.033
Not until I find her mother
and the rest of my family.

05:20.033 --> 05:22.601
Look like you were looking
for yours, too.

05:22.601 --> 05:28.389
♪

05:28.389 --> 05:30.304
I'd reconsider.

05:30.304 --> 05:32.132
This is no place
for kids.

05:32.132 --> 05:36.266
♪

05:36.266 --> 05:37.964
Morgan: Grace, I hope
you can hear me.

05:37.964 --> 05:39.487
Look, I don't know
how much longer

05:39.487 --> 05:41.141
I can keep doing this
without you.

05:41.141 --> 05:42.838
I...

05:44.666 --> 05:46.320
...did what you asked.

05:46.320 --> 05:47.756
I did.

05:47.756 --> 05:51.281
I got Mo someplace safe,
but she needs you.

05:51.281 --> 05:53.588
She needs you,
and I need you.

05:53.588 --> 05:56.374
'Cause I'm scared.

05:56.374 --> 05:58.680
Scared, so I need
my family.

06:02.771 --> 06:06.296
I need --Man: Is somebody
up there?

06:06.296 --> 06:08.995
I could really use
some help down here!

06:15.871 --> 06:18.178
[Zipper rasping]

06:20.833 --> 06:22.530
Evening.

06:22.530 --> 06:24.358
[Blow lands]

06:24.358 --> 06:31.670
♪

06:31.670 --> 06:39.025
♪

06:39.025 --> 06:41.723
Don't be a hero.Okay, okay.

06:41.723 --> 06:43.551
I don't know
what you want,

06:43.551 --> 06:47.337
but whatever it is,
we can work it out.

06:47.337 --> 06:50.906
You gotta give me
my little girl back.

06:50.906 --> 06:54.214
She don't belong to you,
just like all the others didn't.

06:54.214 --> 06:55.476
Others?
What others?

06:55.476 --> 06:56.738
The kids you took.

06:56.738 --> 06:59.219
I did not take
anybody's kid.

06:59.219 --> 07:00.873
Where are they?

07:00.873 --> 07:02.788
♪

07:02.788 --> 07:06.182
Just give me back my daughter,
and you will never see us again.

07:06.182 --> 07:12.580
♪

07:12.580 --> 07:14.669
Get in that hole.

07:14.669 --> 07:16.366
Bury him.[Muffled grunt]

07:16.366 --> 07:18.630
Morgan: Ow!
Why are you doing this?

07:18.630 --> 07:21.459
So every other shithead
can see what happens

07:21.459 --> 07:24.984
when they come here
and steal our kids from us.

07:24.984 --> 07:27.421
[Morgan grunts]

07:27.421 --> 07:29.162
That's it.
Cover him up.

07:29.162 --> 07:31.643
It's what he deserves.Morgan: No, please.

07:31.643 --> 07:33.558
Please!

07:33.558 --> 07:35.211
Man: Hey![Gunshots]

07:35.211 --> 07:37.257
[Grunting, indistinct shouting]

07:37.257 --> 07:39.172
[Gunshots, bodies thudding]

07:41.217 --> 07:43.655
[Baby crying]

07:49.661 --> 07:52.011
[Woman speaking indistinctly]

07:52.011 --> 07:54.317
[Crying continues]

07:57.146 --> 08:00.672
Whoever you are,
thank you for saving my life.

08:00.672 --> 08:02.500
Woman: I'm not here
to save you.

08:09.115 --> 08:11.334
They thought I was you.

08:11.334 --> 08:13.772
That baby is
everything to me.

08:13.772 --> 08:15.948
I'm not gonna let you
take her.

08:15.948 --> 08:18.907
♪

08:18.907 --> 08:20.735
She's better off with me
than you.

08:20.735 --> 08:23.825
And you'll get over it.

08:23.825 --> 08:25.566
I did.

08:25.566 --> 08:26.828
♪

08:26.828 --> 08:27.873
[Gun cocks]

08:27.873 --> 08:29.483
[Gunshot]

08:29.483 --> 08:33.139
♪

08:33.139 --> 08:35.228
[Inhales deeply]

08:35.228 --> 08:38.797
♪

08:38.797 --> 08:40.625
Stop.

08:40.625 --> 08:41.669
[Gun cocks]

08:41.669 --> 08:42.714
Please, stop.

08:42.714 --> 08:43.889
[Gunshot]

08:43.889 --> 08:45.760
I'll kill you
if you follow us.

08:45.760 --> 08:52.158
♪

08:52.158 --> 08:58.686
♪

08:58.686 --> 09:05.171
♪

09:06.564 --> 09:08.870
[Walkers growling,
footsteps approaching]

09:18.488 --> 09:20.099
Oriole, I'm approaching
the drop.

09:20.099 --> 09:21.361
Do you copy?

09:21.361 --> 09:22.841
Man: We copy.

09:27.019 --> 09:28.716
Come on.

09:30.370 --> 09:33.852
[Birds calling, water lapping]

09:42.556 --> 09:44.819
[Hammer clatters]

09:44.819 --> 09:46.081
You're late.

09:46.081 --> 09:47.474
We found some new eggs.

09:47.474 --> 09:49.258
Getting them
processed now.

09:49.258 --> 09:50.912
How long is that
gonna take?

09:50.912 --> 09:52.610
As long as it takes.

09:53.219 --> 09:55.264
[Baby fusses]

09:55.264 --> 09:57.571
Ready?

09:57.571 --> 09:59.486
Hey, come on.

10:01.183 --> 10:03.708
[Baby crying]

10:03.708 --> 10:05.405
You hungry, baby girl?

10:13.543 --> 10:14.806
Here you go.

10:17.983 --> 10:19.288
[Walkie-talkie clicks]

10:19.288 --> 10:22.117
Ava: Jim, are you out there?

10:22.117 --> 10:23.553
Jim, can you hear me?

10:23.553 --> 10:25.251
Do you copy?

10:25.251 --> 10:28.167
We need you, Jim.

10:28.167 --> 10:30.343
This baby needs you.

10:33.215 --> 10:35.957
I got a lead on a new egg,
Oriole.

10:35.957 --> 10:38.394
I'll leave this one
in the birdhouse
and go check it out.

10:38.394 --> 10:40.092
Copy that.

10:42.398 --> 10:44.531
I know you miss
your daddy,

10:44.531 --> 10:50.580
but you're gonna be
better off without him.

10:50.580 --> 10:52.670
[Growling]

11:04.594 --> 11:07.206
[Walkie-talkie clicks] Jim, are you --

11:07.206 --> 11:09.251
Jim, I need --

11:09.251 --> 11:11.166
Hello?

11:11.166 --> 11:12.994
Who is this?

11:12.994 --> 11:15.605
Just someone who wants to help.
I heard your message.

11:15.605 --> 11:16.868
Where are you?

11:16.868 --> 11:18.739
[Walkers growling]

11:18.739 --> 11:20.654
How do I know you're not
the one who's been taking

11:20.654 --> 11:22.743
everybody's kids?

11:22.743 --> 11:24.789
I'm a mother myself.
You can trust me.

11:24.789 --> 11:26.573
I know how hard it is.

11:26.573 --> 11:30.055
I just want my baby
to be okay.

11:30.055 --> 11:32.231
They will. You just have to
tell me where you are.

11:32.231 --> 11:33.928
Can you do that?

11:33.928 --> 11:37.149
♪

11:37.149 --> 11:38.977
[Growls]

11:38.977 --> 11:42.632
♪

11:42.632 --> 11:44.983
[Grunting]

11:44.983 --> 11:47.507
[Breathing heavily]

11:50.684 --> 11:52.338
[Inhales deeply]

11:52.338 --> 11:54.862
[Air hissing]

12:06.352 --> 12:08.049
Are you still there?

12:08.049 --> 12:10.791
I'll tell you where I am
if you're really gonna help me.

12:10.791 --> 12:13.054
Of course I am.
Where are you?

12:13.054 --> 12:16.144
You can understand what --

12:16.144 --> 12:19.408
It's hard to know who to trust,
especially with --

12:19.408 --> 12:21.323
Turn off the walkie.

12:21.323 --> 12:24.152
Are you there? He--Hand over your gun.
Right now.

12:24.152 --> 12:26.459
♪

12:26.459 --> 12:28.113
You're making
a big mistake.

12:28.113 --> 12:31.594
Not as big as the one you made
when you took my daughter.

12:31.594 --> 12:33.074
Drop your weapon.

12:33.074 --> 12:34.728
Turn yourself around.

12:34.728 --> 12:39.820
♪

12:39.820 --> 12:41.256
Where is she?

12:41.256 --> 12:42.736
Somewhere you'll never
find her.

12:42.736 --> 12:43.955
That's the wrong answer.

12:43.955 --> 12:45.739
Where the hell's
my oxygen?

12:45.739 --> 12:48.786
Someplace you'll never find it,
not unless you take me to her.

12:48.786 --> 12:49.961
You don't know
who you're dealing with.

12:49.961 --> 12:51.876
Somebody who's gonna
run out of air.

12:51.876 --> 12:53.312
I'm the least
of your problems.

12:53.312 --> 12:54.835
The people I'm with?

12:54.835 --> 12:56.576
They'll kill you in ways
you can't even imagine.

12:56.576 --> 12:59.579
If you wanna keep breathing,
you should get moving.

12:59.579 --> 13:03.365
♪

13:03.365 --> 13:05.193
You know, you can still
get out of this.

13:05.193 --> 13:06.847
I said --
Those people?

13:06.847 --> 13:08.675
If they find out you've
interfered with an egg --

13:08.675 --> 13:10.155
An egg?

13:10.155 --> 13:11.983
That's what you call the kids
that you steal?

13:11.983 --> 13:13.636
Not stealing.
Rescuing.

13:13.636 --> 13:15.464
From what?

13:15.464 --> 13:18.076
Parents who think they can
give their kids what they need.

13:18.076 --> 13:19.773
Oh, but you think
you can?

13:19.773 --> 13:21.514
If you saw where I'm from,
you'd get it.

13:21.514 --> 13:23.037
[Coughs weakly]

13:23.037 --> 13:25.257
Where exactly
are you from?

13:25.257 --> 13:27.912
And why are you taking these
kids that don't belong to you?

13:36.703 --> 13:38.705
[Inhales deeply]

13:42.796 --> 13:44.842
Voice [over intercom]:
Have you considered our offer?

13:44.842 --> 13:47.061
I'll do what you asked.

13:47.061 --> 13:49.455
But you have to hold up
your end of the deal.

13:49.455 --> 13:52.371
[Coughs]

13:52.371 --> 13:54.503
We will.

13:54.503 --> 13:57.115
How do I know?

13:57.115 --> 14:02.990
The only reason you're still
breathing is because of us.

14:02.990 --> 14:05.123
What's your name?

14:05.123 --> 14:08.039
[Breathing heavily]

14:08.039 --> 14:09.518
Madison.

14:09.518 --> 14:11.303
Not anymore.

14:11.303 --> 14:14.828
We will tell you who you're
going to be from now on.

14:14.828 --> 14:17.700
♪

14:17.700 --> 14:19.398
We're too late.

14:21.530 --> 14:23.228
And what does that mean?

14:23.228 --> 14:24.925
She's already rescued.

14:24.925 --> 14:26.753
My people came sooner
than I expected.

14:33.760 --> 14:35.414
No.

14:37.372 --> 14:39.635
[Dramatic music plays]

14:39.635 --> 14:46.642
♪

14:46.642 --> 14:49.341
You kidding me?
Are you with PADRE?

14:49.341 --> 14:51.909
♪

14:51.909 --> 14:55.434
What do you know
about PADRE?

14:55.434 --> 14:57.653
Let's move.

14:57.653 --> 14:59.351
Let's go.

14:59.351 --> 15:02.963
♪

15:02.963 --> 15:04.182
Which way
would they go?

15:04.182 --> 15:05.879
That baby's better off
without you.

15:05.879 --> 15:07.707
You don't get to decide
what's best for my family.

15:07.707 --> 15:09.404
I already did.

15:11.885 --> 15:13.539
I used to be
just like you.

15:13.539 --> 15:15.671
[Walker growling]

15:15.671 --> 15:23.331
♪

15:23.331 --> 15:26.117
[Grunting]

15:26.117 --> 15:28.336
You are nothing like me.

15:28.336 --> 15:30.034
Not anymore.

15:30.034 --> 15:32.166
[Grunting]

15:32.166 --> 15:36.214
♪

15:36.214 --> 15:38.912
Get off me.
Let me go.

15:38.912 --> 15:41.045
[Breathing heavily]

15:41.045 --> 15:47.486
♪

15:47.486 --> 15:49.183
Oh, dear God.

15:49.183 --> 15:55.276
♪

15:55.276 --> 15:58.236
You're Madison Clark.

15:58.236 --> 16:00.890
How do you know
my name?

16:00.890 --> 16:04.024
Jesus.

16:04.024 --> 16:06.766
Your kids.

16:06.766 --> 16:08.724
Your kids told me.You're full of shit.

16:08.724 --> 16:10.770
No, you died.

16:10.770 --> 16:13.207
That's what they said,
and I saw the stadium.

16:13.207 --> 16:16.341
My kids...

16:16.341 --> 16:18.212
they're alive?

16:18.212 --> 16:22.173
♪

16:22.173 --> 16:24.349
I will tell you
everything I know,

16:24.349 --> 16:27.091
in exchange
for my daughter.Yeah.

16:27.091 --> 16:30.268
There's only one way PADRE's
ever gonna give her back to you.

16:30.268 --> 16:33.488
You're gonna have to help me
rescue someone else's kid.

16:33.488 --> 16:35.186
Take the place
of yours.

16:35.186 --> 16:36.448
No, I'm not doing that.

16:36.448 --> 16:38.711
The kid's gonna be
better off.

16:38.711 --> 16:40.887
What, there's no other way
to give them what they want

16:40.887 --> 16:43.890
without taking some child
away from its family?

16:43.890 --> 16:46.023
There isn't. No.

16:46.023 --> 16:47.894
[Coughing]

16:47.894 --> 16:52.464
♪

16:52.464 --> 16:55.206
What if the kid
isn't born yet?

16:55.206 --> 16:57.643
Would PADRE be interested
in somebody who's pregnant?

16:57.643 --> 16:59.732
Maybe.

16:59.732 --> 17:01.603
Because that woman
you were talking to
on the walkie is pregnant,

17:01.603 --> 17:03.431
and she's not doing
so good.

17:03.431 --> 17:06.391
♪

17:06.391 --> 17:08.306
And I know where she is.

17:08.306 --> 17:13.093
♪

17:13.093 --> 17:14.921
You sure you're ready
to go down that road?

17:14.921 --> 17:16.749
Will I get
my daughter back?

17:16.749 --> 17:18.272
Yeah, you will.

17:18.272 --> 17:20.448
And PADRE -- they'll be able
to look after her

17:20.448 --> 17:22.755
and her baby, right?Yeah.

17:22.755 --> 17:25.627
Then I'm not taking a child
away from its mother, so...

17:25.627 --> 17:27.368
♪

17:27.368 --> 17:28.804
...so yeah.

17:28.804 --> 17:34.767
♪

17:34.767 --> 17:40.686
♪

17:40.686 --> 17:43.210
[Inhales deeply]

17:43.210 --> 17:46.257
♪

17:53.220 --> 17:54.743
[Inhales deeply]

17:54.743 --> 17:56.223
You get smoke
in your lungs

17:56.223 --> 17:58.443
trying to escape
from that stadium?

17:58.443 --> 18:00.097
Is that why
you need this?

18:00.097 --> 18:01.794
Something like that.

18:04.144 --> 18:06.277
Way I heard it,
there was no way

18:06.277 --> 18:08.540
you could have gotten out
of that place alive.

18:08.540 --> 18:10.411
I'm full of surprises.

18:10.411 --> 18:12.152
What else did my kids
tell you?

18:12.152 --> 18:14.067
Oh, quite a bit.

18:14.067 --> 18:16.374
And you are not
what I imagined.

18:16.374 --> 18:17.636
You don't know anything.

18:17.636 --> 18:19.725
You're stealing kids.Rescuing.

18:19.725 --> 18:22.119
Oh, is that you talking,
or PADRE?

18:22.119 --> 18:23.555
What do you know
about PADRE?

18:23.555 --> 18:25.600
You didn't answer
my question before.

18:25.600 --> 18:28.081
I know they're putting out
radio messages.

18:28.081 --> 18:29.691
I know that
nobody can find them,

18:29.691 --> 18:32.172
and I know that Alicia
was looking for them.

18:32.172 --> 18:33.826
Why was Alicia looking
for them?

18:33.826 --> 18:36.829
I'm not telling you anything
more until I get my kid back.

18:36.829 --> 18:38.613
You think you're doing
the right thing,

18:38.613 --> 18:41.268
fighting to get her back,
but she's in the right place.

18:41.268 --> 18:43.836
Believe me.
Why?

18:43.836 --> 18:46.186
Because we can give her
a life people like you can't.

18:46.186 --> 18:47.492
People like me?

18:47.492 --> 18:48.710
Parents.

18:48.710 --> 18:50.538
You couldn't even
feed her.

18:50.538 --> 18:52.714
I would've found food.

18:52.714 --> 18:54.977
Well, it looked to me like you
were barely scraping by

18:54.977 --> 18:57.719
out there
on your own.

18:57.719 --> 18:59.547
It's my daughter.

18:59.547 --> 19:01.158
Her mother --
she's coming.

19:01.158 --> 19:02.594
[Sighs] What difference
is that gonna make?

19:02.594 --> 19:04.248
You don't know
what we endured, okay?

19:04.248 --> 19:06.772
We survived the bombs.

19:06.772 --> 19:08.469
You were in Galveston?

19:08.469 --> 19:10.254
Nick and Alicia
were there too?
I told you --

19:10.254 --> 19:12.343
I'm not telling you
anything more about them.

19:12.343 --> 19:14.519
I'm just saying that
our family have gotten

19:14.519 --> 19:16.216
through worse than this.

19:16.216 --> 19:18.697
Family is not the answer.
It's the problem.

19:18.697 --> 19:20.699
That's what PADRE's
figured out.

19:20.699 --> 19:23.267
That's why what they're building
is different.

19:23.267 --> 19:26.574
You're the woman who put her
life on the line for her family.

19:26.574 --> 19:29.273
What the hell
happened to you?

19:29.273 --> 19:31.100
Is this the place?

19:31.100 --> 19:33.538
Yeah, this is it.
So, what now?

19:33.538 --> 19:35.366
We go in,
we tell her the truth.

19:35.366 --> 19:37.585
And what's that?That we'll take her
to a place

19:37.585 --> 19:40.458
where her baby
will be taken care of.

19:40.458 --> 19:43.983
And then what happens to her
after her baby's born?

19:43.983 --> 19:45.419
She doesn't need
to know.

19:45.419 --> 19:47.856
I need to know.

19:47.856 --> 19:49.728
No, you don't.

19:57.126 --> 20:00.260
How can you do this
to people?

20:00.260 --> 20:02.219
You get used to it.

20:02.219 --> 20:04.308
[Inhales deeply]

20:05.134 --> 20:08.181
I did what you asked.

20:08.181 --> 20:10.836
Now it's your turn.

20:10.836 --> 20:14.492
[Breathing heavily]

20:14.492 --> 20:17.408
Voice [over intercom]:
More.

20:17.408 --> 20:19.627
What did you say?

20:19.627 --> 20:21.760
One time isn't enough.

20:21.760 --> 20:24.023
We're gonna need you
to keep doing it.

20:24.023 --> 20:29.376
♪

20:29.376 --> 20:34.642
♪

20:34.642 --> 20:36.383
Morgan: Ava?

20:38.864 --> 20:41.170
Ava, you there?

20:41.170 --> 20:43.042
What are you
doing here?

20:43.042 --> 20:46.132
Hey.
I, um...

20:46.132 --> 20:49.918
I found somebody
I think can help.

20:49.918 --> 20:52.356
Who are you?We spoke on the walkie.

20:52.356 --> 20:54.749
Morgan told me
where you were.

20:54.749 --> 20:56.273
I just want Jim.

20:56.273 --> 20:58.057
Is that
the baby's father?

21:00.364 --> 21:02.540
This house, it belonged
to my family.

21:02.540 --> 21:04.368
I was born here.

21:04.368 --> 21:06.457
I thought
I'd be safe here.

21:06.457 --> 21:09.155
Well, we can help you
and your baby.

21:09.155 --> 21:10.896
How?

21:10.896 --> 21:13.159
Place I'm from, it's safe,
it's good people.

21:13.159 --> 21:16.858
It's the kind of place a kid
would dream about growing up.

21:16.858 --> 21:19.121
Sounds too good
to be true.

21:19.121 --> 21:20.732
It's for real.

21:20.732 --> 21:23.952
It's the best shot our kids
have for a future.

21:23.952 --> 21:26.868
They even got Morgan's kid
in there, don't they, Morgan?

21:26.868 --> 21:28.783
Morgan:
Yeah, that's right.

21:28.783 --> 21:31.351
I didn't think it was possible
for a place like it to exist,

21:31.351 --> 21:33.658
but it does.

21:33.658 --> 21:35.486
What's it called?

21:35.486 --> 21:37.183
PADRE.

21:43.276 --> 21:44.973
I'll get my things.

21:51.589 --> 21:53.939
Tell me what's gonna happen
to her once the baby's born.

21:53.939 --> 21:55.375
A little late,
don't you think?

21:55.375 --> 21:57.246
Well, you didn't
answer before.

21:57.246 --> 21:58.944
So, what happens?

21:58.944 --> 22:01.599
You know -- otherwise you would
have pressed for an answer.

22:01.599 --> 22:03.035
They get split up.

22:03.035 --> 22:04.732
And why is that?

22:04.732 --> 22:06.821
Because that's
how PADRE works.Yeah, but why?

22:06.821 --> 22:09.041
How does that give the kids
their best shot?

22:09.041 --> 22:11.652
You're looking at this
all wrong.

22:11.652 --> 22:14.699
The way we see each other,
the things we do for each other,

22:14.699 --> 22:16.396
PADRE's rewritten the book
on all of it.

22:16.396 --> 22:19.399
And what does that
look like?

22:19.399 --> 22:21.053
No attachments.

22:21.053 --> 22:22.968
No connections.

22:22.968 --> 22:24.839
I'm not doing this.

22:24.839 --> 22:27.146
I've seen a mother
lose her baby once before.

22:27.146 --> 22:30.454
I don't want to see that
ever again.

22:30.454 --> 22:32.717
Then you'll never see
your daughter again.

22:32.717 --> 22:37.852
♪

22:37.852 --> 22:39.637
Everything alright?

22:39.637 --> 22:41.508
Yeah.
It is for me.

22:41.508 --> 22:42.988
♪

22:42.988 --> 22:45.643
How about you, Morgan?

22:45.643 --> 22:47.775
No, everything's fine.
It's fine.

22:47.775 --> 22:50.125
We should just get you to PADRE.
That's what we should do.

22:50.125 --> 22:51.779
Okay. Yeah.

22:51.779 --> 22:55.000
♪

22:55.000 --> 22:57.524
[Indistinct voices]

22:57.524 --> 22:58.743
Shit.

22:58.743 --> 23:00.179
What?
They found me.

23:00.179 --> 23:01.441
Is there a back way
out of here?

23:01.441 --> 23:02.877
Why are they
after you?

23:02.877 --> 23:05.010
I pissed them off trying
to save some kids.

23:05.010 --> 23:06.577
Now how the hell
do we get out of here?

23:06.577 --> 23:08.013
Yeah, follow me.

23:08.013 --> 23:10.015
♪

23:13.061 --> 23:15.499
[Growling]

23:15.499 --> 23:18.806
♪

23:18.806 --> 23:20.112
Madison:
Wait. Wait.

23:20.112 --> 23:21.374
Come on.
We gotta keep going.

23:21.374 --> 23:22.636
[Inhales deeply]

23:22.636 --> 23:24.029
Let me have it.
No way.

23:24.029 --> 23:26.423
Come on.

23:26.423 --> 23:28.512
Come on.
The beach is this way.

23:28.512 --> 23:30.165
[Grunts]

23:30.165 --> 23:32.037
[Growling]

23:32.037 --> 23:37.042
♪

23:37.042 --> 23:38.522
You okay?I'm fine.

23:38.522 --> 23:40.306
Oh, you're hurt.
Did you get bit?

23:40.306 --> 23:41.612
No, it's from the vines.
I'm good to keep moving.

23:41.612 --> 23:42.700
Come on.
Aah!

23:42.700 --> 23:44.223
Oh, we gotta stop.

23:44.223 --> 23:45.790
If they catch up with us,
they're gonna kill us.

23:45.790 --> 23:47.705
If something happens
to this baby because of us --

23:47.705 --> 23:49.576
I'm fine. It's fine.
Let's just go. Please.

23:49.576 --> 23:51.839
He's right.
If something happens,
it's on me.

23:51.839 --> 23:53.885
Where can we go?

23:53.885 --> 23:55.713
There?
That crypt?

23:55.713 --> 23:56.931
Ava: Yeah.
Yeah, yeah.

23:56.931 --> 23:58.672
Okay, come on.

23:58.672 --> 24:00.718
[Ava groans]

24:00.718 --> 24:04.635
♪

24:04.635 --> 24:07.725
Okay.
Let's get that closed.

24:07.725 --> 24:10.249
♪

24:10.249 --> 24:12.251
[Breathing heavily]

24:12.251 --> 24:14.601
[Doors creak, bang]

24:14.601 --> 24:16.211
Here.

24:16.211 --> 24:18.083
[Scraping]

24:18.083 --> 24:22.261
♪

24:22.261 --> 24:23.828
It's gonna be okay.

24:26.787 --> 24:28.659
What's that?Heart rate monitor.

24:28.659 --> 24:30.138
Just to make sure
nothing's wrong.

24:30.138 --> 24:32.314
I'm fine. Really.
The baby's fine, too.

24:32.314 --> 24:34.534
Just --
Who was out there?

24:34.534 --> 24:36.144
Who's after you?

24:36.144 --> 24:38.669
[Device beeps, whirs]

24:40.888 --> 24:43.195
What is it?

24:43.195 --> 24:45.023
I can't get
a heartbeat.

24:48.200 --> 24:50.463
PADRE --
they have doctors?

24:50.463 --> 24:52.117
Yes.
Morgan:
Then get them here.

24:52.117 --> 24:54.641
Listen. Stop.
You're making this worse.

24:54.641 --> 24:56.817
[Whirring continues]

24:59.733 --> 25:01.996
Can't hear it?
You can't hear the heartbeat?

25:04.738 --> 25:06.000
No.

25:06.000 --> 25:08.481
[Whirring stops]

25:08.481 --> 25:10.048
So keep looking.

25:10.048 --> 25:13.312
She's not pregnant.
She never was.

25:13.312 --> 25:14.618
I don't understand.

25:14.618 --> 25:15.836
She's tricking us.

25:15.836 --> 25:18.317
Why?
To get me to take you to PADRE?

25:18.317 --> 25:19.971
Is that what you thought
would happen?

25:19.971 --> 25:21.363
Is that true?

25:21.363 --> 25:22.930
Are you not pregnant?

25:22.930 --> 25:24.715
Oh, it doesn't matter.
Tie her up.

25:24.715 --> 25:27.239
Leave her some food and water.
She'll only slow us down.

25:27.239 --> 25:29.067
You really don't remember?

25:29.067 --> 25:33.027
♪

25:33.027 --> 25:34.681
You took my daughter.

25:34.681 --> 25:37.162
♪

25:37.162 --> 25:39.120
A year ago.

25:39.120 --> 25:42.341
♪

25:42.341 --> 25:44.343
Told me
it was for the best.

25:44.343 --> 25:46.345
♪

25:46.345 --> 25:49.217
Oh, shit, you
really don't remember.

25:49.217 --> 25:51.742
She was 6.

25:51.742 --> 25:54.658
Her name was Odessa.

25:54.658 --> 25:57.661
She cried when you pulled her
from me on the beach.

25:59.880 --> 26:02.317
What she told you --
it's not true.

26:02.317 --> 26:04.798
He knows exactly
what's going on.

26:04.798 --> 26:06.757
We still have time to get out
of here before they find us.

26:06.757 --> 26:08.019
You need me to take me
to her.

26:08.019 --> 26:10.021
Your plan never
would've worked.

26:10.021 --> 26:11.892
They'd have checked
for a heartbeat
before we got on the boat.

26:11.892 --> 26:13.459
They'd have checked for one
when we arrived.

26:13.459 --> 26:14.982
They'd have checked for one
every day you were there.

26:14.982 --> 26:17.289
I need to see her.
She needs to see me.

26:17.289 --> 26:21.249
If she's not pregnant
and there's no baby,

26:21.249 --> 26:23.034
how are we
getting Mo back?

26:23.034 --> 26:25.166
♪

26:25.166 --> 26:27.038
We're not.

26:27.038 --> 26:28.909
Even with a trade,
there was no guarantee.

26:28.909 --> 26:30.737
You were gonna trade me
for your kid?

26:30.737 --> 26:32.391
You told me that
we would get her back.

26:32.391 --> 26:33.653
I said we might.

26:33.653 --> 26:36.264
♪

26:36.264 --> 26:38.179
Hey.

26:38.179 --> 26:41.269
You need to find a way
to get me to my kid,

26:41.269 --> 26:44.969
or you will never know
where your children are.

26:44.969 --> 26:47.188
You think
that's a threat?

26:47.188 --> 26:49.234
I want my kid.

26:49.234 --> 26:51.149
And you want yours.

26:51.149 --> 26:53.238
That's the thing,
Morgan.

26:53.238 --> 26:55.066
I don't want
to find them.

26:55.066 --> 26:57.198
♪

26:57.198 --> 27:00.158
I'm never gonna
see them again.

27:00.158 --> 27:03.291
And that's okay.

27:03.291 --> 27:06.164
I told you
I got over it before.

27:06.164 --> 27:07.905
I wasn't lying.

27:07.905 --> 27:09.863
No.

27:09.863 --> 27:13.345
No, you are just saying that,
and we had a deal.

27:13.345 --> 27:14.781
So I could get
what I wanted from you,

27:14.781 --> 27:16.609
which was her.

27:16.609 --> 27:20.874
♪

27:20.874 --> 27:23.181
Why else would you be doing
all of this?

27:23.181 --> 27:28.490
♪

27:28.490 --> 27:30.101
[Inhales deeply]

27:30.101 --> 27:39.763
♪

27:39.763 --> 27:41.678
Voice [over intercom]:
Not yet.

27:41.678 --> 27:44.115
We need you to rescue more.

27:44.115 --> 27:48.946
♪

27:48.946 --> 27:50.599
Ava:
You have kids?

27:50.599 --> 27:53.646
♪

27:53.646 --> 27:56.780
We're all doing what we're doing
for our own reasons.

27:56.780 --> 27:59.130
You know them?You really can't help me?

27:59.130 --> 28:03.090
Be smart.
Let's go before they find us.

28:03.090 --> 28:04.352
Whoa!
Easy now!

28:04.352 --> 28:07.442
[Air hissing, canister clanking]

28:07.442 --> 28:14.232
♪

28:14.232 --> 28:16.800
[Gun cocks]

28:16.800 --> 28:18.932
First thing in my
grand-daddy's will.

28:18.932 --> 28:21.456
To be buried with his
favorite hunting gun.

28:21.456 --> 28:23.807
Said he wanted to be prepared
in case he didn't end up

28:23.807 --> 28:25.896
in front
of the pearly gates.

28:25.896 --> 28:27.724
I don't think
you will, either.

28:27.724 --> 28:30.683
[Door rattling, walker growling]

28:30.683 --> 28:32.641
Let's just take it easy.

28:32.641 --> 28:35.862
I know you're angry, but we
gotta get out of here alive.

28:35.862 --> 28:38.169
Only way we're gonna
find our kids, right?

28:38.169 --> 28:40.954
I have another way.

28:40.954 --> 28:43.870
You might not want to see
your kids,

28:43.870 --> 28:46.177
but I don't think
you want them to die.

28:46.177 --> 28:48.005
♪

28:48.005 --> 28:49.702
Are you there?

28:49.702 --> 28:52.270
The ones looking
for the collector?

28:52.270 --> 28:53.488
Man: Who's this?

28:53.488 --> 28:55.012
Someone like you.

28:55.012 --> 28:56.796
Someone she stole
a child from.

28:56.796 --> 28:58.537
What do you want?

28:58.537 --> 29:01.235
I just found a way to motivate
her to do what we want.

29:01.235 --> 29:02.628
But I'm gonna need
your help.

29:02.628 --> 29:04.456
I'm listening.It's not gonna work.

29:04.456 --> 29:07.764
♪

29:07.764 --> 29:10.027
Tell him
where her kids are.

29:10.027 --> 29:11.768
I can't help you.

29:11.768 --> 29:14.292
Where I'm from, they don't
give a shit what I think.

29:14.292 --> 29:15.554
I'm waiting.
What is it?

29:15.554 --> 29:16.990
You better find a way
to make them.

29:16.990 --> 29:18.339
You heard me.

29:18.339 --> 29:21.255
Tell him
where her kids are.

29:22.909 --> 29:24.998
Tell him where to find
her goddamn kids!

29:24.998 --> 29:27.000
I can't.I will shoot you.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.177
And your daughter
will never see you again.

29:30.177 --> 29:32.092
So just tell him
where they are.

29:32.092 --> 29:33.920
She's right.
This is not gonna work.

29:33.920 --> 29:35.792
Why not?Because...

29:40.709 --> 29:42.668
Because
they're already dead.

29:45.671 --> 29:47.804
I'm sorry.
I really am.

29:47.804 --> 29:50.763
But your kids...

29:50.763 --> 29:52.809
they're gone.

29:52.809 --> 29:54.767
Hey!

29:54.767 --> 29:56.900
You said they were alive.
You said you knew
where they were.

29:56.900 --> 29:58.727
I said that so I'd get
what I wanted from you.

29:58.727 --> 30:00.555
You're lying.I wouldn't lie about
something like that.

30:00.555 --> 30:02.862
You don't know anything
about my kids.

30:02.862 --> 30:04.472
You never did.I do.

30:04.472 --> 30:05.996
Madison, I do.

30:05.996 --> 30:08.085
I know
that Nick got shot.

30:08.085 --> 30:10.130
♪

30:10.130 --> 30:11.871
Victor, Alicia,
Luciana --

30:11.871 --> 30:14.178
we were all there
when it happened.

30:14.178 --> 30:16.310
We buried him ourselves.

30:16.310 --> 30:18.530
[Breathing heavily]

30:18.530 --> 30:24.144
♪

30:24.144 --> 30:25.711
And Alicia?

30:25.711 --> 30:29.671
♪

30:29.671 --> 30:32.631
She got bit by a walker
not so long ago.

30:32.631 --> 30:35.808
She had to amputate,
took her own arm off,

30:35.808 --> 30:40.247
but she didn't do it in time,
and the infection set in.

30:40.247 --> 30:44.295
But she fought it for months,
longer than anybody I know.

30:44.295 --> 30:45.992
But the last time
I saw her --
Ah!

30:45.992 --> 30:48.908
...last time
I spoke to her...

30:48.908 --> 30:50.823
No.

30:50.823 --> 30:53.260
...the last time
I talked to her...

30:53.260 --> 30:55.610
♪

30:55.610 --> 30:57.917
...she was close
to the end.

30:57.917 --> 31:00.006
[Sobs] No.

31:00.006 --> 31:06.752
♪

31:06.752 --> 31:08.406
I'm sorry.

31:08.406 --> 31:18.068
♪

31:20.897 --> 31:23.421
[Walkers growling]

31:23.421 --> 31:33.039
♪

31:33.039 --> 31:42.657
♪

31:42.657 --> 31:44.921
At least 30 walkers
out there.

31:44.921 --> 31:46.705
More on the way.

31:46.705 --> 31:48.185
Man [over walkie-talkie]:
Are you there?

31:48.185 --> 31:49.882
I repeat --
are you there?

31:49.882 --> 31:53.494
They're still waiting
on your deal.

31:53.494 --> 31:55.235
Ava: They could still
get us out.

31:55.235 --> 31:56.976
Why aren't you answering?

31:56.976 --> 31:58.456
We're willing
to make that deal.

31:58.456 --> 32:00.371
You can't give them
what you promised.

32:00.371 --> 32:02.547
They're liable to kill us.
They already tried to kill me.

32:02.547 --> 32:05.463
Did she hurt you?

32:05.463 --> 32:07.639
Where are --[Switch clicks]

32:07.639 --> 32:09.728
How long
before they find us?

32:09.728 --> 32:11.251
Property's big.

32:11.251 --> 32:12.818
If they're still at the house,
it could take hours.

32:12.818 --> 32:14.863
Walkers ain't gonna make it
easy for us.

32:14.863 --> 32:16.996
We're gonna have to fight
our way through 'em

32:16.996 --> 32:19.564
and hope we get out
before the posse finds us.

32:19.564 --> 32:21.435
It's gonna take
all of us.

32:27.615 --> 32:30.705
Madison,
we're gonna need you.

32:30.705 --> 32:32.446
Look, I'm sorry I didn't
tell you the truth

32:32.446 --> 32:35.188
about your kids
at the beginning.

32:35.188 --> 32:38.713
I just did
what I thought I had to.

32:38.713 --> 32:40.977
[Growling continues,
doors rattling]

32:46.330 --> 32:49.681
What were they doing
when they died?

32:49.681 --> 32:54.294
♪

32:54.294 --> 32:58.255
Nick was going through
a bad patch when I met him.

32:58.255 --> 32:59.908
Alicia, too.

32:59.908 --> 33:01.867
They thought
that you were gone.

33:01.867 --> 33:03.173
But he was making
the first steps

33:03.173 --> 33:05.131
towards something better,
you know,

33:05.131 --> 33:08.047
and, well,
that's when it happened.

33:08.047 --> 33:11.920
♪

33:11.920 --> 33:16.316
A-Alicia --
how did she get bit?

33:16.316 --> 33:18.057
The bombs we were
talking about --

33:18.057 --> 33:20.494
she was trying to stop them
from going off.

33:20.494 --> 33:22.018
She survived
the explosion.

33:22.018 --> 33:23.497
She helped me,
my little girl,

33:23.497 --> 33:24.933
and some people
that we cared about

33:24.933 --> 33:26.805
escape the fallout, and...

33:26.805 --> 33:29.938
♪

33:29.938 --> 33:32.637
Like I said, she fought
the infection

33:32.637 --> 33:34.465
for as long
as she could.

33:34.465 --> 33:36.119
But you didn't
see her die?

33:36.119 --> 33:39.905
I did not.
I had to leave with Mo.

33:39.905 --> 33:42.647
She could still be
out there.

33:42.647 --> 33:44.779
People don't survive bites.

33:44.779 --> 33:47.043
Yeah, but Alicia was different.
We know that.

33:47.043 --> 33:48.957
Maybe she found a way.

33:48.957 --> 33:52.309
Even if she did,
I don't want to find her.

33:52.309 --> 33:54.224
♪

33:54.224 --> 33:55.660
Why?

33:55.660 --> 33:57.879
♪

33:57.879 --> 34:00.273
Voice [over intercom]:
We think it's time.

34:00.273 --> 34:04.103
You've rescued more children
than any other Collector.

34:04.103 --> 34:06.192
We'll help you
find yours now.

34:06.192 --> 34:12.155
♪

34:12.155 --> 34:18.030
♪

34:18.030 --> 34:19.684
No.

34:19.684 --> 34:23.340
♪

34:23.340 --> 34:25.211
I don't want to find them.

34:25.211 --> 34:32.088
♪

34:32.088 --> 34:35.569
I was willing to die
at the stadium,

34:35.569 --> 34:37.267
so my kids
could see what --

34:37.267 --> 34:40.661
what I was building
was worth fighting for.

34:40.661 --> 34:44.752
But if they knew what I was
doing to find them...

34:44.752 --> 34:47.451
PADRE played me
from the start.

34:47.451 --> 34:49.453
Made me do things
I didn't want to,

34:49.453 --> 34:54.719
so when I could finally
get them back, I'd say no.

34:54.719 --> 34:57.417
If you didn't want
to find them,

34:57.417 --> 35:00.725
why are you still
taking kids for PADRE?

35:00.725 --> 35:03.641
Because I knew what they'd do
if I walked away.

35:03.641 --> 35:05.295
What?They'd find
Nick and Alicia

35:05.295 --> 35:09.212
and make them do
what I wouldn't anymore.

35:09.212 --> 35:11.997
But I don't have to worry
about that now.

35:11.997 --> 35:13.825
[Growling continues]

35:13.825 --> 35:16.001
[Doors banging]

35:17.829 --> 35:21.485
I wish I knew that
before I took your daughter.

35:21.485 --> 35:25.706
[Gunfire]

35:25.706 --> 35:28.231
The posse.They found us.

35:28.231 --> 35:30.972
They get through that door,
they're gonna kill us both.

35:30.972 --> 35:32.626
Man: Open up.
We know you're in there.

35:32.626 --> 35:33.932
She saved me once before.

35:33.932 --> 35:35.281
They think
we're working together.

35:35.281 --> 35:37.196
If we give her up,
maybe they'll spare you.

35:37.196 --> 35:39.677
No, we need her to get our kids,
and so do they.

35:39.677 --> 35:42.245
I don't think they're gonna
see it that way.

35:42.245 --> 35:43.942
[Doors rattle]

35:43.942 --> 35:46.597
Man: If you're hiding her,
we're gonna have a problem.

35:46.597 --> 35:49.339
♪

35:49.339 --> 35:50.775
Let them in, Morgan.

35:50.775 --> 35:52.211
Don't sacrifice yourself
for me.

35:52.211 --> 35:53.821
I'm not doing it
for you.

35:53.821 --> 35:55.649
I'm doing it so you can get
my daughter back for me.

35:55.649 --> 35:57.303
I can't get
your daughter back.

35:57.303 --> 35:59.523
I can't get yours back, either.
I can't undo any of this.

35:59.523 --> 36:01.612
Yes, you can.
You just need to find a reason.

36:01.612 --> 36:02.874
[Banging]Man: Hey!
Open the door!

36:02.874 --> 36:04.397
Morgan.They're gonna kill you.

36:04.397 --> 36:05.964
There's only one way to
show them you're not with me.

36:05.964 --> 36:07.139
Man:
Open the damn door!

36:07.139 --> 36:08.923
Okay, wait!

36:08.923 --> 36:10.795
Just wait.

36:10.795 --> 36:15.713
♪

36:15.713 --> 36:17.541
We're gonna open the door.

36:17.541 --> 36:22.328
♪

36:22.328 --> 36:24.939
We're gonna hand her
over to you.

36:24.939 --> 36:27.377
Sorry.

36:27.377 --> 36:30.249
It's the only way to live
to see your daughter one day.

36:30.249 --> 36:35.211
♪

36:35.211 --> 36:37.474
[Bench scraping]

36:37.474 --> 36:46.396
♪

36:46.396 --> 36:48.659
Hands where we can
see them.

36:48.659 --> 36:55.492
♪

36:55.492 --> 37:02.281
♪

37:02.281 --> 37:03.761
Remember me?

37:03.761 --> 37:05.806
You took my boy
last winter.

37:05.806 --> 37:08.635
♪

37:08.635 --> 37:11.769
You'll remember me now.

37:11.769 --> 37:13.901
Get up.
And start digging.

37:13.901 --> 37:15.947
High tide's in less
than two hours.

37:15.947 --> 37:18.428
♪

37:33.617 --> 37:35.706
You made the right call.

37:39.666 --> 37:41.102
Morgan:
What did you do to her?

37:41.102 --> 37:43.583
Wilt: Left her to watch
the tide come in.

37:43.583 --> 37:46.456
Worse when you can
see it coming.

37:46.456 --> 37:48.109
What'd she tell you?Not much.

37:48.109 --> 37:49.807
But she didn't need to.

37:49.807 --> 37:52.940
We found this
in her pack.

37:52.940 --> 37:55.203
We know when they're coming
to pick her up.

37:55.203 --> 37:56.814
Put it on.

37:56.814 --> 37:58.294
Why would I do that?

37:58.294 --> 37:59.904
We're gonna surprise
her friends at the beach.

37:59.904 --> 38:02.341
Bury them all in the sand
if we have to.

38:02.341 --> 38:04.038
Someone will talk.

38:04.038 --> 38:06.084
Someone will tell us
where our kids are.

38:13.657 --> 38:15.180
There a problem?

38:15.180 --> 38:16.877
This is not gonna get
our kids back.

38:16.877 --> 38:18.792
This is gonna get
everybody killed.

38:22.448 --> 38:24.407
Let him go.

38:24.407 --> 38:26.104
That's not
how this works.

38:26.104 --> 38:27.497
They took our kids.

38:27.497 --> 38:29.325
So why are we fighting
each other?

38:31.457 --> 38:33.154
Just let him go.

38:36.419 --> 38:39.117
You know what happens
if you get in our way.

38:39.117 --> 38:41.685
I know. I won't.

38:52.957 --> 38:55.916
Don't go with them.

38:55.916 --> 38:58.092
You don't have to.

38:58.092 --> 38:59.964
I have to get
to my kid, Morgan.

39:01.748 --> 39:03.620
I have to do something.

39:08.102 --> 39:11.410
Odessa lost this the day
before Madison took her.

39:11.410 --> 39:14.370
I promised I'd find it
and I'd get it back to her.

39:16.633 --> 39:18.504
I'm not gonna break
that promise.

39:21.420 --> 39:23.074
I know.

39:23.074 --> 39:32.823
♪

39:32.823 --> 39:42.702
♪

39:42.702 --> 39:44.748
[Groans lightly]

39:44.748 --> 39:54.801
♪

39:54.801 --> 39:57.064
[Breathing heavily]

39:57.064 --> 39:58.936
[Coughing]

39:58.936 --> 40:00.981
♪

40:00.981 --> 40:03.549
[Walkers growling]

40:03.549 --> 40:10.861
♪

40:10.861 --> 40:18.216
♪

40:18.216 --> 40:25.658
♪

40:25.658 --> 40:27.704
[Baby crying]

40:27.704 --> 40:35.015
♪

40:35.015 --> 40:42.327
♪

40:42.327 --> 40:44.024
[Growling]

40:44.024 --> 40:53.817
♪

40:53.817 --> 41:03.609
♪

41:03.609 --> 41:10.050
♪

41:10.050 --> 41:13.227
[Wheezing]

41:13.227 --> 41:15.360
You don't deserve
to go out like this.

41:15.360 --> 41:17.144
I told you,
I can't help you.

41:17.144 --> 41:18.929
That's not why I'm here.

41:18.929 --> 41:21.453
♪

41:21.453 --> 41:23.281
You know, when I met your kids,
I was in a place

41:23.281 --> 41:25.588
not too different
from where you are now.

41:25.588 --> 41:28.112
I wanted to get away
from everything and everybody.

41:29.243 --> 41:32.159
But meeting Nick
and Alicia,

41:32.159 --> 41:34.901
seeing what you had
given them,

41:34.901 --> 41:36.381
they were a big part of

41:36.381 --> 41:39.079
when things started
turning around for me.

41:39.079 --> 41:43.301
So, in a way,
I kinda owe you.

41:43.301 --> 41:44.998
So, I think you should
show the people

41:44.998 --> 41:47.000
who did this to you
that they're wrong.

41:47.000 --> 41:49.089
You can fight for the people
you care about

41:49.089 --> 41:51.788
without losing
yourself.

41:51.788 --> 41:54.486
I can't.
Hey.

41:54.486 --> 41:57.924
No one's gone
until they're gone.

41:57.924 --> 42:01.885
Alicia said that was
something you used to say.

42:01.885 --> 42:03.582
That's the thing.

42:03.582 --> 42:07.760
Everything I've done --
I amgone.

42:07.760 --> 42:09.196
[Coughs]

42:11.024 --> 42:12.896
Hang on.
Hang on.

42:12.896 --> 42:15.420
I got your tanks.

42:15.420 --> 42:19.119
[Wheezing]

42:19.119 --> 42:22.688
[Walkers growling]

42:22.688 --> 42:28.520
♪

42:28.520 --> 42:30.609
Oh, dear God,
they're all...

42:30.609 --> 42:35.222
♪

42:35.222 --> 42:37.616
I told them not to go
to the dock.

42:37.616 --> 42:39.662
♪

42:39.662 --> 42:41.359
Hang on, Madison!

42:41.359 --> 42:44.623
♪

42:44.623 --> 42:46.059
[Weakly] Morgan.

42:46.059 --> 42:48.322
Morgan!

42:48.322 --> 42:50.368
[Growling]

42:50.368 --> 42:57.854
♪

42:57.854 --> 43:05.339
♪

43:05.339 --> 43:07.864
No. No, no.

43:07.864 --> 43:10.780
♪

43:10.780 --> 43:12.172
Morgan!

43:12.172 --> 43:14.087
Never should've
pulled you into this.

43:14.827 --> 43:18.483
[Growling]

43:18.483 --> 43:20.137
Morgan.

43:20.137 --> 43:29.407
♪

43:29.407 --> 43:38.764
♪

43:38.764 --> 43:48.034
♪

43:48.034 --> 43:49.383
I'm sorry.

43:49.383 --> 43:58.784
♪

43:58.784 --> 44:01.265
[Inhales deeply]

44:06.923 --> 44:09.447
What the hell was that?

44:09.447 --> 44:12.145
She's dead because
of something I did.

44:12.145 --> 44:14.800
Not gonna see her daughter
because of me.

44:14.800 --> 44:17.716
No, she's dead
because of PADRE.

44:17.716 --> 44:19.544
You were just ready
to give up.

44:19.544 --> 44:22.242
What's changed?

44:22.242 --> 44:24.462
I'm gone, Morgan.

44:24.462 --> 44:26.290
I'm gone, but you're not.

44:26.290 --> 44:30.686
♪

44:30.686 --> 44:33.340
I'll help you get
to your daughter.

44:33.340 --> 44:35.342
I'll help you show PADRE
they're wrong.

44:35.342 --> 44:36.648
And then what?

44:36.648 --> 44:38.389
I don't know.
But I wasn't lying.

44:38.389 --> 44:40.217
The only way
you're gonna get to PADRE...

44:40.217 --> 44:42.393
♪

44:42.393 --> 44:45.701
...is if you take them
another child.

44:45.701 --> 44:47.615
There's gotta be
another way.

44:47.615 --> 44:49.705
♪

44:49.705 --> 44:51.315
There isn't.

44:51.315 --> 45:00.846
♪

45:00.846 --> 45:02.761
No, there is.

45:02.761 --> 45:05.242
♪

45:05.242 --> 45:07.287
It just means
we can't fail.

45:07.287 --> 45:15.295
♪

45:15.295 --> 45:23.347
♪

45:23.347 --> 45:25.131
Guard: Who's he?

45:25.131 --> 45:28.004
Collector.
He has something to offer.

45:28.004 --> 45:29.440
I don't see anything.

45:29.440 --> 45:30.920
Morgan:
I got information.

45:30.920 --> 45:34.097
There's rafts out there
with people on them.

45:34.097 --> 45:35.794
What kind of people?

45:35.794 --> 45:38.057
Ones we might want.There's children.

45:38.057 --> 45:39.929
Pregnant woman.

45:39.929 --> 45:43.367
I can tell you more, but, um,
you gotta let me go with you.

45:43.367 --> 45:49.460
♪

45:49.460 --> 45:51.114
Get in.

45:51.114 --> 45:59.644
♪

45:59.644 --> 46:08.218
♪

46:08.218 --> 46:10.786
Where the hell
are we going?

46:10.786 --> 46:13.136
Where is PADRE?

46:13.136 --> 46:15.181
Been meaning
to tell you.

46:15.181 --> 46:17.314
♪

46:17.314 --> 46:19.185
I don't know.

46:19.185 --> 46:28.847
♪

46:28.847 --> 46:38.422
♪

46:38.422 --> 46:47.997
♪

46:51.348 --> 46:54.742
[Suspenseful music plays]

46:54.873 --> 46:57.876
This episode is all
about family --

46:58.007 --> 46:59.704
Morgan and what
he thinks for Mo

46:59.835 --> 47:02.794
and it's the return
of a character

47:02.925 --> 47:05.318
who gave up everything
for her family --

47:05.449 --> 47:07.233
Madison Clark.

47:07.364 --> 47:10.280
It is very exciting to have Kim
come back to the show

47:10.410 --> 47:13.239
and continue to tell her story.

47:13.370 --> 47:14.937
Very exciting to get to do it

47:15.067 --> 47:16.895
through the eyes
of Morgan Jones,

47:17.026 --> 47:19.332
a character who knows
about Madison Clark,

47:19.463 --> 47:21.987
but has never actually
crossed paths with her,

47:22.118 --> 47:23.728
and it's just such lightning
in a bottle

47:23.859 --> 47:26.296
to get these two characters
together in this way.

47:26.426 --> 47:28.037
She's better off with me
than you.

47:28.167 --> 47:29.038
And you'll get over it.

47:29.168 --> 47:30.039
[Mo crying]

47:30.169 --> 47:31.779
I did.

47:31.910 --> 47:33.869
The audience starts to put it
together, as Morgan does,

47:33.999 --> 47:36.132
is that Madison is actually
this person that...

47:36.262 --> 47:37.524
Hey, stop!

47:37.655 --> 47:38.917
...the people
who buried him were after

47:39.048 --> 47:42.268
and that she is
stealing children?

47:42.399 --> 47:43.966
Which leaves us
with this huge question --

47:44.096 --> 47:46.751
why in the hell
is Madison Clark

47:46.882 --> 47:50.276
stealing kids and taking kids
away from their parents.

47:50.407 --> 47:53.323
-[Crying]
-Someone who family
was everything to her,

47:53.453 --> 47:56.369
why is she now
ripping families apart?

47:56.500 --> 47:57.805
I know you miss your daddy.

47:57.936 --> 48:00.504
But you're going to be
better off without him.

48:00.634 --> 48:03.333
Someone who has been
working for PADRE

48:03.463 --> 48:05.857
and what we come
to learn about PADRE is

48:05.988 --> 48:09.600
that they are an organization
that has a philosophy --

48:09.730 --> 48:10.993
family is a weakness,

48:11.123 --> 48:13.430
family is something
to fight against .

48:13.560 --> 48:15.606
We start to then gain
some insight

48:15.736 --> 48:18.870
into the way that PADRE
has manipulated Madison

48:19.001 --> 48:21.090
into collecting children
for them.

48:21.220 --> 48:22.874
One time isn't enough.

48:23.005 --> 48:24.658
We're going to need you
to keep doing it.

48:24.789 --> 48:26.530
We see how they
dangled the carrot

48:26.660 --> 48:28.140
of reuniting her
with her children,

48:28.271 --> 48:29.576
but then break her
to the point

48:29.707 --> 48:31.404
where she wouldn't want
to be around them.

48:31.535 --> 48:33.580
And it gives us insight
into Madison's way

48:33.711 --> 48:35.234
of justifying things,
as a character,

48:35.365 --> 48:37.758
but it also gives us insight
into what PADRE's doing.

48:37.889 --> 48:39.151
You interfered
with an egg.

48:39.282 --> 48:40.457
An egg?

48:40.587 --> 48:42.546
That's what you call
the kids that you steal?

48:42.676 --> 48:44.461
Not stealing,
rescuing.

48:44.591 --> 48:46.115
We have heard about PADRE

48:46.245 --> 48:48.073
in a positive light.

48:48.204 --> 48:49.553
What is PADRE?

48:49.683 --> 48:50.989
Something better.

48:51.120 --> 48:53.774
Or, at least,
the possibility of it.

48:53.905 --> 48:55.951
But what we find out here
is that, yes,

48:56.081 --> 48:58.127
maybe it is trying
to rebuild civilization,

48:58.257 --> 49:00.825
but it's trying to do it
in a pretty unconventional way,

49:00.956 --> 49:04.263
so I don't think this is
what anyone was expecting.

49:04.394 --> 49:05.395
Get off me.

49:05.525 --> 49:06.962
Let me go.

49:07.092 --> 49:10.574
Madison is shocked
when Morgan recognizes

49:10.704 --> 49:13.490
the names on the tattoos
on her wrists

49:13.620 --> 49:15.840
because Madison
hasn't encountered anyone

49:15.971 --> 49:18.147
who knows her kids
for a very long time.

49:18.277 --> 49:20.888
From Morgan's perspective,
seeing Madison is literally

49:21.019 --> 49:23.239
like coming face-to-face
with a ghost.

49:23.369 --> 49:24.370
You're Madison Clark.

49:24.501 --> 49:26.198
♪

49:26.329 --> 49:27.939
How do you know my name?

49:28.070 --> 49:31.464
Madison's point of view
of Morgan is pretty complicated

49:31.595 --> 49:34.641
because she knows
that there is not a whole lot

49:34.772 --> 49:38.080
that they can do
to get Mo back,

49:38.210 --> 49:39.907
now that she's been handed
over to PADRE.

49:40.038 --> 49:41.648
There's only one way
PADRE's ever going

49:41.779 --> 49:42.910
to give her back to you.

49:43.041 --> 49:44.086
You're going to have
to help me rescue

49:44.216 --> 49:45.609
someone else's kid

49:45.739 --> 49:47.872
to take the place
of yours.

49:48.003 --> 49:49.526
No, I'm not doing that.

49:49.656 --> 49:51.571
What, there's no other way
to give them what they want

49:51.702 --> 49:52.920
without taking some child

49:53.051 --> 49:55.619
away from its family?There isn't. No.

49:55.749 --> 49:57.229
There's a lot
that Madison can relate to

49:57.360 --> 49:59.014
on an emotional level.

49:59.144 --> 50:01.016
Morgan is in a position

50:01.146 --> 50:03.409
where he is willing
to kidnap a pregnant woman

50:03.540 --> 50:05.281
to make a trade
for his own child.

50:05.411 --> 50:08.762
He's sacrificing
kind of his ideals for Mo.

50:08.893 --> 50:10.895
I've seen a mother
lose her baby once before.

50:11.026 --> 50:12.853
I don't want to see that
ever again.

50:12.984 --> 50:14.464
Then you'll never see
your daughter again.

50:14.594 --> 50:15.856
Goldberg:
Morgan doesn't want to think

50:15.987 --> 50:18.816
he is going down
the same path as Madison,

50:18.946 --> 50:20.687
although Madison
does warn him and say,

50:20.818 --> 50:22.689
"Are you sure you want to go
down this path?"

50:22.820 --> 50:24.387
Everything alright?

50:24.517 --> 50:25.997
Yeah, it is for me.

50:26.128 --> 50:28.391
Goldberg: Morgan realizes
it is a very slippery slope.

50:28.521 --> 50:30.175
It's fine. We should
just get you to PADRE.

50:30.306 --> 50:31.524
That's what
we should do.Okay.

50:31.655 --> 50:33.526
Goldberg:
When family is leveraged,

50:33.657 --> 50:36.181
you'll do a lot of things
that you don't want to do.

50:36.312 --> 50:37.878
Man:
Check the house first.

50:38.009 --> 50:39.402
Shit.What?

50:39.532 --> 50:40.751
They found me.

50:40.881 --> 50:41.926
Man: Who's this?

50:42.057 --> 50:43.536
Someone she stole
a child from.

50:43.667 --> 50:44.494
What do you want?

50:44.624 --> 50:45.930
I just found a way

50:46.061 --> 50:47.192
to motivate her
to do what we want.

50:47.323 --> 50:48.672
I'm listening.It's not gonna work.

50:48.802 --> 50:50.891
♪

50:51.022 --> 50:52.850
Tell him where to find
her goddamn kids!

50:52.980 --> 50:55.287
I can't. Because
they're already dead.

50:55.418 --> 50:58.508
Goldberg: Seeing Madison
have that emotional reaction

50:58.638 --> 51:00.771
